This paper deals with the biases introduced by filtering, ranking, and recommendation algorithms in online information consumption. It analyzes a massive dataset of web traffic to quantify two kinds of bias: homogeneity bias and popularity bias. The paper also focuses on traffic to news sites. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), followed by cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences), cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity), and cs.MM (Multimedia).
